@startuml
title Use Case 3: Conversation Navigation

actor User
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Server as "Server"

== Open conversation ==
User -> GUI: Click conversation (conversationId)
GUI -> Client: Request conversation view\n(conversationId)

Client --> Server: Inform server of conversation switch(conversationID)
alt Client has < 200 messages loaded for conversationId
  Client -> Server: GetRecentMessages(conversationId, limit=200)
  Server --> Client: Most recent up to 200 messages\n(or fewer if total < 200)
  Client -> Client: Store messages in conversation cache
else Client already has enough messages loaded
  Client -> Client: Read messages from conversation cache
end

Client --> GUI: Provide messages for display
GUI -> GUI: Render messages

== Infinite scroll / paging older messages ==
loop User scrolls up (load older messages as needed)
  User -> GUI: Scroll up

  alt Scroll position >= 80% through loaded messages (toward older)
    GUI -> Client: Request older messages\n(conversationId)
    alt Client needs more (not already cached)
      Client -> Server: GetOlderMessages(conversationId,\n olderThan=oldestLoadedMessageId,\n limit=200)
      Server --> Client: Up to 200 older messages\n(or fewer if none left)
      Client -> Client: Append older messages to cache
    else Client already has older messages cached
      Client -> Client: Read older messages from cache
    end

    Client --> GUI: Provide additional messages
    GUI -> GUI: Prepend older messages to view
  else Not near threshold
    GUI -> GUI: Continue displaying loaded messages
  end
end
@enduml
